# Gamification System — Implementation Plan

## Goal

Add a level/XP gamification system to OOSkills with a **progressive circular ring around the profile picture** showing XP progress and level number — visible in the landing page navbar and student dashboard. Built **frontend-only with mock data**, using **icons only** (no emojis), matching the existing Oxford Blue + Gold design system.

---

## Key Design Decisions

- **Profile Avatar Ring**: SVG circular progress arc around every profile picture occurrence, with a small level number badge. The ring fills proportionally to XP progress toward the next level (gold stroke on dark track).
- **Mock Data**: All data comes from a `gamificationSlice` with hardcoded mock values. No backend endpoints needed now.
- **Icons Only**: All achievements and UI elements use Heroicons/Lucide icons, never emojis.
- **Sound Effects**: Audio feedback on level-up, achievement unlock, and XP gain — using small MP3/WAV files in `public/sounds/`. User can mute via a preference toggle.
- **Rich Animations**: Confetti particles on level-up, floating "+XP" numbers on XP gain, slide-in toasts for achievements — all via Framer Motion.
- **Consistent UI**: All new components use the existing color palette (`oxford`, `gold`, `cream`, `silver`), Tailwind dark mode classes, Framer Motion animations, and `rounded-xl` / `rounded-lg` patterns.

---

