## XP & Level System Reference

| Level | Title (EN) | Total XP | XP for Level |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Beginner | 0 | — |
| 2 | Apprentice | 100 | 100 |
| 3 | Student | 300 | 200 |
| 4 | Explorer | 600 | 300 |
| 5 | Scholar | 1,000 | 400 |
| 6 | Expert | 1,500 | 500 |
| 7 | Master | 2,200 | 700 |
| 8 | Champion | 3,000 | 800 |
| 9 | Legend | 4,000 | 1,000 |
| 10 | Genius | 5,500 | 1,500 |

---

## Implementation Phases

### Phase 1 — LevelAvatar + Core Slice
Create `gamificationSlice` with mock data, build `LevelAvatar` component with SVG ring, integrate into all 4 avatar locations.

### Phase 2 — Dashboard Enhancements
Add `XPProgressBar`, `StreakCounter`, achievement cards to dashboard page.

### Phase 3 — Pages
Build achievements page, leaderboard page, add sidebar navigation items.

### Phase 4 — Sound Effects & Animations
Add `LevelUpModal` with confetti + sound, `XPGainToast` with floating numbers, `AchievementToast` with slide-in, `useSoundEffects` hook, sound asset files.

### Phase 5 — Translations & Final Polish
Add translations for all 3 languages. Final browser testing across all features.

---

## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing
1. Check `LevelAvatar` renders correctly in Header (desktop + mobile) and StudentHeader
2. Verify SVG ring fills proportionally and level badge displays
3. Verify dashboard XP bar, streak counter, and achievements render
4. Trigger level-up modal — verify confetti animation + sound plays
5. Trigger XP gain toast — verify floating number animation + sound
6. Trigger achievement toast — verify slide-in + sound
7. Test mute toggle — verify sounds are silenced
8. Test dark mode for all new components
9. Test RTL (Arabic) layout
10. Navigate to `/dashboard/achievements` and `/dashboard/leaderboard`
